bio: To Aditi, yoga goes beyond movement and can bring freedom and joy into life. Having lived and practiced yoga in India and NYC, Aditi’s style of teaching is anchored in tradition, creativity, fun, and flowing, challenging her students to grow from the inside out. She has been named one of NYC’s best instructors, led exciting events like a live 2000+ person class in Time Square, and helped to launch Peloton Yoga and Meditation in 2018! Deeply connected to storytelling and music, Aditi shines when teaching artist series classes, and her own signature series Flow and Let Go.
background: Yoga is a practice that allows us to thread together the external with the internal - the physical workings with the mental, emotional, spiritual.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Yoga is a direction - you are aiming for a posture. You don’t have to get there today, but you do have to start, you do have to try. When I began practicing, I could not get my hands to the ground.'], ['Outside of Peloton ', 'I’m a total nerd about health and love to read about science. I also love to travel the world and I lived in Mumbai for a few years and love it there. I’ve climbed Kilimanjaro, and love to trek and hike.'], ['', '']]
quote: Practice makes progress.
name: Aditi Shah

bio: Adrian is a powerhouse instructor with an unexpected tender side. A native New Yorker with bold Bronx energy, Adrian is a competitive sprinter—but he’s not all speed and strength. Adrian's lighthearted sense of humor is what really shines through his coaching. His goal is to encourage others and bring joy through fitness. When he’s not at the gym, you can find Adrian perfecting his craft behind the camera. Adrian is a passionate photographer and finds peace in the creative process.
short_bio: Adrian is a powerhouse instructor with an unexpected tender side. A native New Yorker with bold Bronx energy, Adrian is a competitive sprinter—but he’s not all speed and strength. His lighthearted sense of humor shines through his coaching.
background: Working out should feel good! My goal is to empower people to form healthy habits to carry with them for the rest of their lives. I will challenge you, then hit you with positivity. At the end of the day, I want to bring you joy!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I encourage you to embrace being uncomfortable. That’s where growth happens. I try not to take myself too seriously, though. My workouts are tough, but I like to lead with humor. I want you to leave with a smile!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Photography has been a growing passion of mine. Fitness requires so much energy, and photography helps me slow down and appreciate small moments. I also love to cook too, because I love to eat!'], ['', '']]
quote: “Never give up because great things take time.”
name: Adrian Williams

bio: I foolishly thought that rowing was like running—just on the water instead of on the track—and hopped in a boat my freshman year. Fortunately, I've never been so happy to be so wrong. I was hooked from that first moment and have dedicated the last 15 years to this sport. I can't wait to share my enthusiasm for rowing with the Peloton community.
short_bio: Alex comes to Peloton Row via the World Championships and the Olympics—but you’ll never meet a more humble, enthusiastic guy. When you row with Alex, you’re guaranteed to learn something new.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', "I never want Members to feel like they have to get through class. I want you to feel that it's an opportunity to push for a little more and find out something about yourself."], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'In my time away from the studio, you can find me scoping out the best new Thai food in town, listening to phenomenal movie soundtracks, or building classic LEGO sets—there is always more space in the apartment!'], ['', '']]
quote: “It doesn’t matter what I do—it matters what I bring out in other people.”
name: Alex Karwoski

bio: Alex Toussaint has a love for fitness, teamwork and discipline rooted in his military school background. With his eye always on the prize, Alex uses the power of positivity to motivate Members to confront their limitations and push past them. In his class, you can expect a well-structured ride, and to walk out feeling his mantra in your bones: “Feel good, look good, do better.”
short_bio:
"Feel good. Look good. Do better! 
… Trust the Process!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Alex’s current class playlist.
background: I approach all my classes like it might be my last one. Watching Members become the best version of themselves truly inspires me to give it my all every ride I teach.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Using my military background, I push my Members to their full potential at all times. I want Members to approach my workout like an athlete, and leave feeling like a champion.\r\n'], ['Outside of Peloton', "When I’m off the Bike I’m on the basketball court or gym. Fitness isn't just my hobby, it’s my life!"], ['', '']]
quote:
Feel good. Look good. Do better! 
… Trust the Process!
name: Alex Toussaint

bio: As a model, dancer, certified health coach, host of the Brooklyn Nets, runner, and the founder of fitness lifestyle brand Love Squad, Ally really does it all. At Peloton as in all of her pursuits, Ally’s goal is to lead by example while empowering people to approach wellness and fitness in a positive light. When she’s not on the Peloton Bike, you can find her flexing her entrepreneurial muscles, or enjoying a good doughnut.
short_bio: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
music_bio: Check out a sample of Ally’s current class playlist.
background: My life goal is to remind the world that we all have one life to live, and together we should live it to the fullest. I believe that what connects us most is the power of sweat, and physically working through things as a team.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'We ride to become boss of the Bike and to remind ourselves that we are the boss of our lives. My classes are designed to make you feel proud and uplifted, both on and off the bike.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I always try find the right balance of fun and work, knowing they don't have to be different things. Off the Bike I love donuts, tennis, basketball, karaoke and parties."], ['', '']]
quote: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
name: Ally Love

bio: Andy takes a technique-centered approach to fitness, drawing on his experience as an accomplished former gymnast and pole vaulter in his home state of Connecticut. A celebrated personal trainer in NYC before joining Peloton, Andy is inspired by the world-class fitness and strength coaches who taught him, and brings his breadth of training knowledge to every workout.
background: My inspiration for teaching is rooted in helping others improve their lives through fitness, as other coaches have done for me, now it’s my turn to pay it forward.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want members to approach my class with an intent to be challenged and grow. I focus on technique and ensure that there is a purpose behind everything I ask of you.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My training also includes gymnastics, kettlebells, Olympic weightlifting, Muay Thai kickboxing, and yoga. I also enjoy watching documentaries, meditation, reading, and listening to Podcasts.'], ['', '']]
quote: Fight Fatigue with Focus.
name: Andy Speer

bio: When Anna first turned to yoga, she felt a switch turn on inside of her. As she built a deeper connection with her mind and body, she began accomplishing things she never knew possible. Moved to share the transformative properties of the practice with others, Anna dove head first into yoga. Anna has crafted a unique teaching style that uses movement and music to help her Members connect to the same healing properties of yoga that she has experienced over the years. Anna is a prominent teacher trainer, workshop leader and instructor in NYC.
short_bio: “Look for balance but always be willing to fall”
background: My classes combine heat building movement with precise, focused instruction for Members to find stability and space in their bodies and minds. Watching Members grow and thrive on the mat and in their lives is what inspires me to teach!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I aim to inspire people to do their best and let go of the results. Yoga is not a competition or performance, it’s just for you (how great is that?). It’s a tool to strengthen your relationship with yourself.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'When I’m not standing on my hands, you can catch me traveling the world whenever, and wherever I can. I enjoy being in nature, hiking, biking and just walking around and taking it all in.'], ['', '']]
quote: Look for balance but always be willing to fall.
name: Anna Greenberg

bio: I’m a first-generation college student, and I’m proud to have broken multiple glass ceilings: I’m a black woman who has won rowing championships, I hold an advanced degree, and I’m a published author. I also run my own rowing academy! I like to keep busy.
short_bio: Ash’s classes are always a party—but when the red lipstick comes out, you’re in for a serious sweat. She’s a Big Ten champion, a seasoned coach, and she instills positivity into every stroke. With Ash, you’ll always leave feeling brighter.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', "I’m excited to bring a party on a rower. We can be weird and goofy and get an amazing workout. If you're gonna sparkle, then sparkle! I’ll challenge you to bust through the glass ceiling, and kick your butt with a smile."], ['Outside of Peloton', "I'm learning to play the ukulele right now. It is red and her name is Ruby. And I love documentaries. Family and community are important to me—I love spending time with my loved ones, and being a cool auntie! "], ['', '']]
quote: “I’m a bull—so when we see red, we boogie!”
name: Ash Pryor

bio: As a refugee child, Assal was often made to feel like she had to prove herself more than others. But her mother always taught her about the power of being herself. A former weightlifter and police officer, she’s learned that true strength is both vulnerability and the ability to get comfortable in the discomfort of hard work. Because a strong body starts with a strong mindset. Now, she’s bringing her passion, precision, dedication, and drive to classes that will motivate you to strengthen your muscles and your mind. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—and that once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
short_bio: A former weightlifter and police officer, Assal Arian knows that a strong body starts with a strong mindset. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
background: I’ve been told I’m too ambitious, too small, too Persian. But it just made me stronger, because my mum showed me the power of being me. And this is what I teach in my classes—the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate others?', 'There is so much power in being a beginner—when you’re ready and motivated to learn is when you really grow. I make my classes a place where everyone feels empowered to try new things and see what they can achieve.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love music. Any kind of music. From reggaeton to hip hop, house, electro to dancehall and flamenco. It helps me lose myself in the moment and find motivation in different places.'], ['', '']]
quote: I’m always trying something new, finding new challenges, getting out of my comfort zone, and working to improve.
name: Assal Arian

bio: Becs joins Peloton from London as an accomplished distance runner and coach who uses the sport as a way to explore the world. From adventurous trails, tropical beaches, and exotic volcanoes, to sub-3:00 marathons and demanding ultramarathons, she’s run across the globe and can’t wait for her next journey on the Peloton Tread. When teaching, Becs shares wisdom from her own training experience to help inspire everyone from first time runners to seasoned athletes. No matter how experienced you are, you’ll leave her class smiling and proud, energized to tackle your next challenge.
short_bio: "Challenge yourself, and be determined to thrive."
background: My inspiration comes from running all around the world! I want to teach the people in my class to love the way running makes them feel. My approach is tough, but I’ll always run with a smile because my passion for the sport is so alive.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I share a lot of my own personal training experiences to relate to people in my classes. I want Members to see that we have the same goals, and are on a journey together.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I train for my own goals, setting myself up for whatever my next race may be. I adore spending time eating my way around cities, so moving to NYC has been a dream and I keep finding amazing new places everywhere I go.'], ['', '']]
quote: Challenge yourself, and be determined to thrive.
name: Becs Gentry

bio: Growing up, Ben was an accomplished athlete who was always looking for the opportunity to run, ride, kick a ball or compete. Working at a prestigious finance firm, Ben found himself daydreaming about his days on the field and in the gym. That inspired him to begin training clients as a side hustle. He quickly gained momentum and decided to take a leap of faith to leave finance behind to pursue his true passion in fitness. Ben is excited to connect through his love of music, coach with Peloton Members around the world, and become a part of their story as they move through challenges on and off the Bike. Ben is based in the UK and teaches cycling & strength.
short_bio: Work hard in silence, let progress be your noise.
background: I love fitness because it has a wonderful way of breaking down barriers for people.
ordered_q_and_as: [[' How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'I love having the opportunity to change someone’s mindset and self-belief. I love to inspire. I love to educate people so they feel fully in control of their own progress.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I found my passion for training through track and field, and have completed marathons and ultra endurance events. Outside of fitness, I’m a huge fan of live music and travel, and am always on the hunt for my next meal.'], ['', '']]
quote: Work hard in silence, let progress be your noise.
name: Ben Alldis

bio: Benny was born in the gym–he lives and breathes fitness. When he's not partying on his Peloton Bike, wowing you with his positive vibes, he's training with his friends and getting inspired by other workouts. Only music can inspire him as much as exercise. And he knows that you get the best out of yourself when you just have some fun. So be yourself and experience how to turn any workout into a party.
short_bio: Benny comes from a real sports family and spent half his life in gyms. In his rides, he combines endurance and technique with fun and entertainment. When you train with Benny, every workout becomes a party.
background: In my workouts you can be anything, but most of all you can be yourself. I want everyone in my rides to have a good time. That's why I became a Peloton instructor.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate others?', 'Fun and entertainment are the most important things in my workouts. I want everyone to enjoy every ride. The rest will just come naturally.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My friends are the most important thing to me. I love fitness and music. If I can combine those three things, then I'm the happiest person in the world."], ['', '']]
quote: Working out with you all is my party.
name: Benny Adami

bio: If there’s one thing that really motivates former boxing instructor Bradley, it’s having the odds stacked against him. The moment someone says he can’t do something, well, that’s all he needs to hear to go out and do it! It’s why he’s often been labelled a rebel as he always manages to find a way to overcome life’s obstacles by doing things his way. After a decade in New York, Bradley is now back in the UK to bring his unique blend of British charm and eternally optimistic attitude to the London cycling studio. He’s a big believer that life is an adventure we shouldn’t take too seriously, so expect him to keep you smiling through his sweat-drenched sessions on the Bike.
short_bio: Boxing fan Bradley believes you’re never beaten, however big the challenge. It’s this approach to life combined with his infectious smile and a love of putting fun at the heart of his classes that will keep you coming back.
background: I want Members to leave my classes with a smile on their face KNOWING they’ve got the beating of whatever challenges they may be facing. However much of an underdog you may feel, there is always a way over that hill.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "FUN is important to me! It becomes really hard to stick to something if you're not enjoying yourself, so I’ll push past whatever excuses you've got, but because you're being equally entertained, you'll hardly notice."], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', "I'm a keen traveller, animal lover and meditator. I've been called a rebel because I love proving people wrong, so you’re welcome to challenge me, but beware, I won't just beat you, I'll also post about it on Instagram!"], ['', '']]
quote: Sometimes you have to fight more than once to win it
name: Bradley Rose

bio:
Callie radiates sunshine. She comes from a large family of athletes, but broke the mold to pursue dance. Years of rigorous ballet training taught her discipline, grace and strength. Her knowledge of technique and emphasis on quality of movement extends to her classes. 

Callie’s workouts are tough, but she’ll make you feel good after every class.
background: Everyone is welcome in my class. I want you to feel comfortable and confident after we work out together.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'We can accomplish anything we put our mind to by instilling confidence. Show up as yourself, and I’ll guide you the rest of the way. Expect to work hard, laugh a little and leave with an undeniable sense of self worth.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'When I’m not at Peloton, you can find me shopping in the pillow aisle or throwing punches in the gym. Nothing makes me happier than spending time with loved ones in the comfort of my own home. '], ['', '']]
quote: “Believe in yourself, and you're halfway there.”
name: Callie Gullickson

bio: Introducing Camila Ramón, Peloton’s newest cycling instructor. Camila is teaching in both Spanish and English, and she’s bringing a whole new energy and positivity to Peloton. You’ll hear it right away with her music choices, and you’ll see it right away with her dance moves. Camila instills positive, powerful perspectives and approaches to life and relationships with fitness, so you’ll never feel more confident than when you ride with her.
background: I was born in Argentina and grew up in Miami. Family is everything to me. I’m deeply connected to my community, and I bring that energy with me to every class, every day. Come ride with me!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I motivate through passion and positivity. I care about every person in my class. I teach you to push boundaries. I want you to discover your strength, and after class, I want you to feel like you can take on anything!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Being outdoors centers me. I love hiking, running and camping with my husband and my pup Rex. I love spending time with my vibrant family and eating dulce de leche while binge-watching netflix.'], ['', '']]
quote: Juntos en esta comunidad somos imparables.
name: Camila Ramón

bio: As the oldest of four siblings, Charlotte has always looked after everyone else. Looking out for and loving herself was something she had to learn first. To her, working out is self-care. As a trained doctor, she knows that every time you work out, you're doing something good for you. Expect Bike classes full of power and positivity—for Charlotte, limits exist only to be overcome.
short_bio: For Charlotte, limits only exist to be overcome. No matter your fitness level, as a trained doctor, she’ll help you discover what you're capable of. Join her in her powerful classes and finish every ride with a proud smile.
background: As a doctor, I know my body inside out. But only through fitness did I learn to also love myself. Don’t be afraid to love yourself and to be proud of you. That’s what I want to pass on to our Members.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Fitness is my medicine—it has the power to change your life. Every time we’re working out together, you’re doing something good for yourself. Leave your life behind, forget all expectations and just give your best.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'From opera to rock to techno–music plays a big part in my life. And that includes both dancing to the sounds of my favorite DJ and relaxing on the couch to my favorite album.'], ['', '']]
quote: Let’s find our limits—and then challenge them together.
name: Charlotte Weidenbach

bio: Chelsea has traveled a unique path to bring her expression of yoga to both the tenured yogi and those who never believed the practice was for them. Chelsea received her Ph.D. in Educational Studies, making it her life's work to study the positive impact that yoga has on communities. Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you, making you happier and healthier in your daily life. Chelsea's teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her as you build strength and confidence.
short_bio: Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you. Her teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her while you build confidence and strength.
background: My intention is to create an environment that leaves Members with a strong sense of belonging and accomplishment. I am inspired by how yoga, music and soulful storytelling can take us on a journey closer to ourselves.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I empower you to embrace the body you are in! Yoga is an opportunity to pour love back into yourself, and can travel with you off the mat and into your life in the form of strength, peace, presence and wisdom.  '], ['Outside of Peloton', 'As a Ph.D. and former school teacher, I bring yoga and education to others. I created a tuition-free space for teen girls to read, write poetry, practice yoga and build a community called Yoga, Literature & Art Camp. '], ['', '']]
quote: I want to be someone people relate to. I’ll encourage you as I push you.
name: Chelsea Jackson Roberts

bio: Christine D’Ercole is a decorated track cyclist who brings this expertise to every Peloton class. Grounded in science, music, grit and grace, Christine believes that at all times you have two tools at your disposal: your breath and your inner monologue. In her class, you can expect Christine to empower Members to break through self-imposed limitations, and embrace their authentic selves and strength, both on and off the Bike.
short_bio: "I AM. I CAN. I WILL. I DO."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Christine’s current class playlist.
background: My classes are grounded in science, grit and grace. I will give you structured formats rooted in 20 years of competitive cycling experience set to playlists that push you farther than you thought possible.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'Every class is an opportunity to put something across the finish line and make yourself proud. By showing up, turning it up and not giving up, we practice real-life skills that translate off the Bike.'], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', 'BIKE RACING!, Wordshop™, writing, cooking, fine wine, scuba diving and photography.'], ['', '']]
quote: I AM. I CAN. I WILL. I DO.
name: Christine D'Ercole

bio: Growing up in Hamburg, Cliff’s first love was football–until music came along. In fact, his love of hip hop saw him become the first German rapper to make it to the semi-finals of the ‘Voice of Germany’. Given he’s used to performing on a stage under the bright lights, it’s no wonder he feels so at home in the Peloton studio. As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy mean you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also feeling re-energised and ready to hit all the high notes. Cliff rides in our London studio and does Bike and Bootcamp classes in German.
short_bio: As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy help you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also being re-energised and ready to take on whatever life has in store for you.
background: I’m inspired by the synergy of music and fitness, it gives me an energy that I just have to pass on. Everyone feels that in every single class I give.
ordered_q_and_as: [['HOW DO YOU MOTIVATE?', 'As an athlete, praise and positive encouragement have always driven me to push myself beyond my limits and perform at my best. With this power, I want to motivate everyone to achieve more and look for fewer excuses. '], ['OUTSIDE OF PELOTON', "When I'm not on the Peloton stage, I spend as much time as possible with my family. My wife and daughter mean everything to me."], ['', '']]
quote: No excuses - Don't look for excuses, find solutions.
name: Cliff Dwenger

bio: A former professional dancer, Cody brings energy, movement and authenticity to everything he does. Born in the West but raised in the South, Cody always dreamed of a life in the big city. Now that he proudly calls NYC home–and the best city in the world–he strives to be the best version of himself while inspiring Members to be the same. Cody reminds everyone in his class to push themselves, but have a good time doing it, because we all need to have a little more fun.
music_bio: Check out a sample of Codys current class playlist.
background: Success happens when you allow yourself to be in the present moment —  when we truly let go of any regret of the past or fear of the future.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'If I am not living my truth in everything I do, then I am not doing it right. I want Members to have fun while they’re working out, and remember that even though it’s challenging, "It’s not that deep!”'], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', 'Outside of Peloton I love to travel and discover the world. Because of my busy life in NYC, I love to find balance and serenity through my meditation practice.'], ['', '']]
quote: Can I do this? ABSOLUTELY!
name: Cody Rigsby
